description: {"blocks":[{"key":"d7p6q","text":"This protocol is intended as a guideline to perform the Real Time PCR (qPCR or rtPCR) procedure to detect and quantify miRNAs. This method use TaqMan® MicroRNA Assays and Applied Biosystems real-time PCR instruments. The assays are preformulated primer and probe sets designed to detect and quantify miRNAs, and can detect and quantify small RNA in 1 to 10 ng of total RNA with a dynamic range of greater than six logs. This protocol works on detecting miRNA from samples that were purified from plasma and serum. The amplified products of the RT procedure must be stored − 15 to − 25 °C, if not used immediately for rtPCR. The aim of this protocol is to use a sequence- specific TaqMan® assay to accurately detect miRNAs.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8et7v","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
